.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "August 2023"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- Simple Unix Shell Program
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[\fIcommand\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBsimple_shell\fR is a basic Unix shell program implemented in C. It provides an interactive command-line interface where users can execute system commands, use built-in commands, and work with environment variables.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fBcommand\fR
The command to be executed by the shell. Can be provided for non-interactive mode.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBexit\fR
Exit the shell.
.TP
\fBenv\fR
Display the environment variables.
.TP
Any other system command
Execute the given system command.
.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
When run without any arguments, \fBsimple_shell\fR enters interactive mode, where it prompts the user for input and executes entered commands.
.SH NON-INTERACTIVE MODE
When provided with a command as an argument, \fBsimple_shell\fR runs in non-interactive mode, executing the given command and then exiting.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run in interactive mode:
.sp
\fI$ ./simple_shell\fR
\fB#cisfun$ ls -l\fR
\fB#cisfun$ exit\fR
.TP
Run in non-interactive mode:
.sp
\fI$ ./simple_shell "ls -l"\fR
.SH NOTES
.TP
This is a basic shell intended for educational purposes.
.TP
Built and tested on Unix-like systems.
.SH AUTHOR
This shell was implemented by \fI[Juan Sebastian Varcercel Chaux and Gilberto Lozano Gutierrez]\fR.
